Defendant Thurston T Faulkner in court with attorney Nicole M Masnica.  Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.   The Court strikes the repeater.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts #2, 3 and 4 are dismissed and read in.       The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS 6 MONTHS  IMPRISONMENT, (consectuve to any other sentence).
  -  1 YEAR 6 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Maintain full time employment and or combination of schooling or any other acitivity deemed appropriate by agent.
*Peform 100 hours community service.
*Not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.


COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 10 MONTHS, First Two months to be served as Straight time.  The next 6 months to be served with non working hours. Last two months (STAYED); to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  Sentence to begin forthwith.   Defendant is remanded into custody. 

DAY REPORT CENTER: 8 MONTHS (consecutive to condition time).

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
